Author: j4jackj
Text: Some people on this sub use it as a way to restrict and not feel as starvey.  So I would be careful jumping on the keto bandwagon where we are, as much as some people are getting results with recovery there, because some are also getting results in enabling the easier carrying on of their restricting.  I worry about warrior diets and Fung diets especially for the "I can't eat normally" population because of the closeness of those to active anorexia and binge-eating anorexia.
